ng JSON components**\\n\\nI’m looking into `JSON.with(MapBuilder)` and `MapReader`. It seems like `beanFrom(CountsMap.class)` might not use the default `_mapBuilder`. That's possibly because `MapReader::_mapType` refers to `CountsMap.class`, while `_mapBuilder(mapType)` returns a new builder based on the `_mapBuilder` field in `JSONReader`. I want to clarify this to understand how the components interact better. There’s a bit to untangle here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_AmwgP8I1UV1zhJXggA6TqDrx|fc_0e7dba2d35ed94200169f029e569088194b68448cfcb1a44ec", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.fasterxml.jackson.jr/jackson-jr-objects/2.21.0/src/test/java/com_fasterxml_jackson_jr/jackson_jr_objects/MapBuilderDefaultDynamicAccessTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import com.fasterxml.jackson.jr.ob.JSON;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class MapBuilderDefaultDynamicAccessTest {\n    @Test\n    void readsEmptyObjectsIntoConfiguredTypedMapImplementations() throws Exception {\n        CountsMap counts = JSON.std.beanFrom(CountsMap.class, \"{}\");\n\n        assertThat(counts).isInstanceOf(CountsMap.class).isEmpty();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void readsSingletonObjectsIntoConfiguredTypedMapImplementations() throws Exception {\n        CountsMap counts = JSON.std.beanFrom(CountsMap.class, \"{\\\"only\\\":99}\");\n\n        assertThat(counts).isInstanceOf(CountsMap.class);\n        assertThat(counts).containsEntry(\"only\", 99);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void readsMultiEntryObjectsIntoConfiguredTypedMapImplementations() throws Exception {\n        CountsMap counts = JSON.std.beanFrom(CountsMap.class, \"{\\\"alpha\\\":1,\\\"beta\\\":2}\");\n\n        assertThat(counts).isInstanceOf(CountsMap.class);\n        assertThat(counts).containsEntry(\"alpha\", 1).containsEntry(\"beta\", 2);\n    }\n", "newText": "import com.fasterxml.jackson.jr.ob.JSON;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.jr.ob.api